    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Pál Várday and Miklós Oláh (Vienna, 16
                    September 1548)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He has received their letter about the capture and
                            imprisonment of the Forgách brothers, and he has already ordered
                            Wolfgang von Puchheim to let them go. Furthermore, he maintains his
                            previous decision, and if they appear at the time he indicated, they may
                            present their cases.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Pater ac Venerabilis,
                    Devoti Fideles nobis Dilecti!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Accepimus litteras<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Ep.
                            688.<ref>olahus.tei.15480915_1</ref></note> fidelitatum ac devotionum
                    Vestras, quibus nobis significarunt de interceptione ac retentione
                        <persName>Sigismundi</persName> et <persName>Ladislai
                        Forgach</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Zsigmond Forgách and
                        László Forgách.</note> iamque propterea commisimus nobili fideli nobis
                    dilecto <persName>Wolfgango libero baroni in Puecham</persName>,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Wolfgang von Puchheim.</note> ut ipsos absque
                    ulla mora cum omni ipsorum comitatu liberos dimittat, prout Devotiones Vestrae a
                    nobis pro sua prudentia humiliter petierunt, <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                            ><del corresp="scriba">et sicuti</del> ipseque a
                            <persName>Puecham</persName> se omnium absque mora facturum
                        recepit</add>. Volentes autem nos insistere deliberationi <del
                        corresp="scriba">huic</del> nostrae <del corresp="scriba"
                    >devotionibus</del>, Fidelitati Vestrae clementer mandamus ac hortamur, quod si
                    citatio quam fieri iusseramus <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">ad praefatos
                            <persName>Forgach</persName> fratres</add> nondum fuerit emanata, ut eam
                    primo quoque tempore expediant, ac exsecutioni demandari curent, ita ut dicti
                        <persName>Sigismundus</persName> et <persName>Ladislaus</persName> fratres
                    ad terminum a nobis praefixum compareant negotium illud nobis <del
                        corresp="scriba">personaliter</del> declaraturi. Quod fidelitati Vestrae
                    gratiose respondere voluimus, facient autem in eis clementem voluntatem
                    nostram.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Datum in <placeName>Nova Civitate</placeName> Austriae 16.
                    Septembris 1548.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Strigoniensi et Zagrabiensi.</p>
